<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Weaken" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Weaken,</orth> 1) tr. to enfeeble, to debilitate: <bibl n="shak. son 23.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 23, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 75</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to become feeble: <cit><quote>his notion --s, his discernings are lethargied,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.248" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 248</bibl></cit>.
